descriptions.value: Jones Lang LaSalle Americas, Inc., (“JLL”) and Compass, Inc. (“Compass”) are pleased to offer the opportunity to acquire a unique, non-rent-controlled multifamily portfolio in Downtown San Francisco, California. 780 Van Ness Avenue and 755 Eddy Street (“Properties” or “Subject”) comprise a 0.45-acre site and are being offered together. The Properties were both developed by current ownership, in 1990 and 2003 respectively, and have been well maintained and operated ever since. As such, the Properties represent a high-quality opportunity for an investor to acquire well-located, stabilized assets in a core San Francisco neighborhood that also offer substantial redevelopment potential. Such redevelopment potential stems in part from the fact the land is not fully developed because the site includes a surface parking lot.780 Van Ness Avenue is a four-story mixed-use building occupying a 0.34-acre parcel with 18 two-bedroom/two-bathroom rental apartments above two ground-floor commercial spaces. In addition to the mixed-use building, this parcel is improved with a surface parking lot. 755 Eddy Street is a five-story residential building occupying a 0.11-acre parcel with a total of 12 rental apartments, consisting of 8 one-bedroom/one-bathroom units and 4 two-bedroom/ two-bathroom units. The Properties are situated adjacent to one another in the northwest corner of the block bounded by Van Ness Avenue, Turk Street, Polk Street, and Eddy Street.The Subject site is located three blocks north of San Francisco City Hall and is surrounded by a wide array of uses including medium-density mid-rise residential, high-rise residential, ground-floor retail, and two-story commercial buildings. The mixed-use 30 Van Ness Avenue project from developer Lendlease, which will create 333 condominiums and nearly a quarter million square feet of commercial office space, is only a half-mile walk from the Properties. This project is set to be among the tallest buildings in the Bay Area and one of the few high- rises expected to rise this year in San Francisco.

descriptions.value: 188 Octavia Consists of One Modern Retail Space Located in an Exciting New Hayes Valley Development Just Off the Bustling Hayes Street Corridor.​ The Space Features Big Windows, and High Ceilings.​ Located Along the Gateway Into San Francisco for Visitors Arriving From the 101 Freeway, 188 Octavia is Sure to Catch the Visitor’s Eye as They Drive Into the Hayes Valley Neighbor-hood.​ 28 Upscale Residential Units Top This Magnificent Space.​
188 Octavia offers studio &a; 2 bedroom apartments in San Francisco, CA! Fantastic amenities + Great location in Lower Haight &a; near Civic Center Plaza. Click for more info!

188 Octavia offers studio & 2 bedroom apartments in San Francisco, CA! Fantastic amenities + Great location in Lower Haight & near Civic Center Plaza. Click for more info!188 Octavia is an apartment community located in San Francisco County and the 94102 ZIP Code. This area is served by the San Francisco Unified attendance zone.

188 Octavia consists of two modern retail spaces located in an exciting new Hayes Valley development just off the bustling Hayes Street corridor. Each space will feature big windows, high ceilings, and contemporary finishes. Located along the gateway into San Francisco for visitors arriving from the 101 freeway, 188 Octavia is sure to catch the visitor’s eye as they drive into the Hayes Valley neighborhood. 28 upscale residential units top these two magnificent spaces, which are expected to be delivered in Spring 2020. Features Two modern retail spaces consisting of approximately 1,562 SF and 998 SF corner retail spaces Spring 2020 Delivery. Each space features high ceilings, big display windows, and great visibility from all visitors coming into San Francisco from the 101 South freeway and the Bay Bridge. Suitable for a variety of uses including restaurant, caf, personal and professional services. Wide storefront with attractive signage opportunities on two exterior sides. Situated at the base of a 28-unit luxury midrise spanning an entire block. Centrally located in Hayes Valley near City Hall, SFJazz Center, Davis Symphony Hall, War Memorial Opera House, and some of the Citys best restaurants and shops such as Absinthe, Ritual Coffee, Marine Layer, Buck Mason, Cala, Souvla, Warby Parker, and more.

descriptions.value: Stream Realty Partners is pleased to present For Sale or Lease 532-536 Sutter Street in San Francisco’s premier Union Square District. The historical asset, previously home to San Francisco Playhouse, boasts tremendous demographics; in a 10-mile radius, there are 1,500,000 people with an average household income of $144,000. The property is zoned as Downtown Retail and has limitless potential: retail, art gallery, entertainment, multifamily, hospitality, restaurant, and/or cannabis dispensary.The building, constructed in 1910 and recently seismically retrofitted, offers three stories and a sizable basement totaling 16,596 SF. This flagship retail location is near the Sutter and Powell intersection and has great access via bus and cable car, both of which are less than 150’ from the front doors. The iconic building has beautiful, exposed brick walls, penthouse office, and rooftop bar potential.Union Square is a major tourist destination in San Francisco, offering one of the largest collections of department stores, upscale boutiques, and art galleries in the United States. It contains 12,000 hotel rooms, 70,000 daytime employees, and roughly 650 buildings. The tenants include the highest end brands in retail: Gucci, Hermes, Tiffany, Neiman Marcus, etc.The property has been issued a permit for cannabis retail and/or consumption. Due to sensitive use restrictions, there are only five cannabis retailers in Union Square, none of which have a consumption lounge.Stream Realty Partners is pleased to present For Sale or Lease 532-536 Sutter Street in San Francisco’s premier Union Square District. Marcus & Millichap has been selected to exclusively market for sale 532 Sutter Street, an architecturally significant retail property constructed in 1910, located within one-and-one-half blocks of Union Square in San Francisco, California.​  This high street retail building is being offered with its three stories and basement totaling approximately ±16,506 square feet.​ It is 100 percent vacant for an owner-user, mixed-use developer, or local or foreign investors interested in acquiring a pride-of-ownership property in the highly desirable Union Square neighborhood.​ The property is situated on an approximately 6,000-square-foot lot and provides over 5,500 square feet of street level retail.​ Current owners have invested approximately $500,000 on seismic retrofitting of the building, providing a stable basis for the property to be developed.​ Sutter Street is one of San Francisco’s main thoroughfares to downtown, with some of the highest traffic volumes passing in front of the property.​ The property at 532 Sutter is located just minutes from central dining and entertainment establishments as well as some of the best shopping the city has to offer.​ This property represents a perfect value-add opportunity for an investor/developer looking to grow in an increasingly appreciating market.​ Booming downtown San Francisco’s limited supply of retail, hotel, and apartment inventory provides a solid foundation for the property’s further appreciation and strong cash flow potential.​ INVESTMENT HIGHLIGHTS  ​Irreplaceable Real Estate  ​Strategic Location  ​Value-Add/Re-Development Opportunity

descriptions.value: Centrally Located South of Market Opportunity 1012 Bryant Street is an opportunity for an owner-user or investor to redevelop a centrally located property in Western SOMA.​ The neighborhood is home to a number of leading technology companies including AirBnb, Twitter, Square, Stripe, Uber, Pinterest among others.​ These tech employers are a principle driver of changing skyline marked by the construction of residential towers and reinvented office and industrial properties.​The building has been owned and occupied for 30+ years by a family home made ceramics business.​ The building layout consists of a large open ground floor space consisting of approximately 1,871 sq ft plus an upper level building was previously used as an office is built-out with several rooms.​ The upper level walks out to the roof potentially allowing the possibility to add a roof deck.​ The building is of wood frame construction, with a stucco facade and a concrete foundation.​ The property is zoned Service/Arts/Light Industrial (SALI) which per the San Francisco Planning Code is largely comprised of low-scale buildings with production, distribution, and repair uses.​ The district is designed to protect and facilitate the expansion of existing general commercial, manufacturing, home and business service, and light manufacturing activities, with an emphasis on preserving and expanding arts activities.​ Nighttime Entertainment is permitted although limited by buffers around RED and RED-MX districts.​ Residential Uses, Offices, Hotels, and Adult Entertainment uses are not permitted, except that certain Affordable Housing Projects are permitted within the district pursuant to Section 846.24 of the Planning Code, and Accessory Dwelling Units are permitted within the district pursuant to subsection 207(c)(4) of the Planning Code.​ The zoning permits numerous uses and the height limit is 40/55-X potentially allowing for expansion of the existing building or construction of new larger building.​

Available September 2020: historic (circa 1895) 101 Montgomery Street, Suite 200 in the Presidio, 19,067 rentable square feet. Located in the park’s Main Post neighborhood, this former barracks has been beautifully renovated as a multi-tenant office building. Suite 200 is a private space and full floor layouts of the top two floors of the building. 100 Montgomery is one of San Francisco's original skyscrapers and set the standard of quality for all succeeding high-rise office buildings. In 2009, Hines completed construction of a new façade for the building, new retail storefronts, and a new lobby designed by the world renowned Robert A.M. Stern Architects. The signature component of this $30 million renovation is new lobby which aggrandizes the already prominent corner of Montgomery and Sutter Streets. It’s dramatic elliptical wall of structural glass defines its modern existence. In addition, a new state-of-the art crystallized glass panel façade system (the first of its kind on the west coast) adorns the building’s skin along with refurbished exterior aluminum decorative panels and stainless steel window mullions. Additionally, the original lobby on Montgomery Street was refurbished. Building amenities include: Deli/carry-out restaurant, Overnight courier drop box, High-speed telecom, Concierge, Recently Refurbished Conference Center with state-of-the-art technology, Copy services, Sundry shop, Fiber optics, Catering, a 16th floor Roof Deck, On-site Gym, and secure bike storage. The 24 hour manned security console monitors all traffic in the building, including retail and tenant traffic and access to both low-rise and high-rise elevator banks. The building also utilizes a keycard entry system for after-hours access. Building hours are 6am - 6pm, Mon - Fri. Ten traction elevators serve the low-rise and high-rise towers, including one freight elevator. There is a sidewalk hydraulic elevator for large deliveries, scheduled in advance. The HVAC system consists of a constant volume system, served by air handling units with chilled water fan coils. There are two environmentally compliant Carrier chillers and two cooling towers. Steam is supplied to perimeter induction units for heating and hot water is used to heat interior zones. Tenant windows on floors 3-25 are operable. Situated one block north of Market Street and adjacent to the Montgomery BART station, the property is easily accessed by all major forms of transportation in the Financial District. Although the building does not have parking on site, there are several parking garages in close proximity.

descriptions.value: Located at the Southeast Corner of Howard Street and Beale Street, the Ground Floor Remodel of 301 Howard Offers Best in Class Space for Premium Food and Beverage Uses and Retailers, 2,100-square-foot Space With Double High Ceilings, Glass Storefront, and an Abundance of Sunlight, Situated Across From the Transbay Terminal and 750,000-square-foot Class a Park Tower Office Building.​ The Space Offers an Unrivaled Combination of Pedestrian Traffic, Public Transportation and Population Density.​ Shell Delivery Available.​ Type 1 Venting Installed

Commercial location available as owner has relocated from area and is selling.​ Formerly used as a construction warehouse and rental apartment above.​ The property is in need of some TLC, but offers 2500 sq ft of 1st floor space and a 1750 sq ft second floor.​ Property will be sold as is.​

A striking addition to the renowned San Francisco skyline, 301 Howard is a Class-A high rise located in the burgeoning South of Market area, two blocks from the Embarcadero BART station and ideally situated for Bay Bridge access. The elegantly designed tower is angled on opposite corners, with stepped-back usable terraces on four of its upper floors linked with round forms rising to mirror the sky. The exterior finish is a reflective glass and aluminum frame curtain wall. Rich Italian marble in light, warm tones dramatized by inlaid black marble tracery and a fine art sculpture are highlights. The upper floors offer magnificent 360-degree views of San Francisco. Building amenities include: deli/sandwich restaurant, gourmet soup shop, sundry shop, ATM, lounge/fitness center, spectacular views, excellent access to transportation and freeways, dedicated parking, and 24-hour security. In addition to the great tenant amenities, perhaps one of the greatest features of 301 Howard is a rooftop terrace offering breathtaking views of the San Francisco Bay. 301 Howard is situated across from the newly-opened $2.2 billion Salesforce Transit Center that serves as a hub for SF Muni, Golden Gate and AC transit, Greyhound, Amtrak and Caltrain. In addition to Salesforce, neighboring tenants include Google and Facebook which in aggregate lease/own approximately 5 million square feet in close proximity to 301 Howard.

Rising forty-three stories tall in the heart of SoMA, these San Francisco luxury rentals offer a brilliant combination of location and elevation, putting the city's most exciting new neighborhood at your door and breathtaking panoramas outside your window. reviews.text: TL;DR is it falls far short of its promises, with a host of unresolved issues and indifferent management.Despite understanding that older apartments may require more maintenance, I am disappointed that the problems I reported upon moving in have yet to be addressed, even after four months. My patience with the staff has been met with apathy. The air gaps in windows and floors have made it impossible to get a good night's sleep, exposing me to cold winds and noise without any signs of improvement. It has become evident that the root of the problem lies not in the building's age but rather in the management's incompetence.During the apartment tour, everything appeared flawless at first glance, but the reality is quite different. The numerous air gaps are just one issue among several. The malfunctioning toilet, combined with misleading information about the premium BOSCH appliances, has been a major source of frustration. Additionally, simple requests, like replacing a broken closet light, took an inexplicable four months and resulted in a cheap, ineffective fixture being installed which is too dim to illuminate a small closet.Whenever the maintenance staff does show up, their efforts are often superficial. When asked what they did to solve the problem, they don’t have an answer and simply shrug. This lack of accountability only adds to the overall dissatisfaction.Regrettably, this luxury rental has provided a subpar experience. Conversations with other tenants have revealed that I am not alone in my dissatisfaction, as several residents have been forced to move out due to unresolved issues.If you're seeking a luxury rental in SF, it would be wise to explore other options that prioritize tenant satisfaction and property maintenance.
reviews.title: The only thing luxurious about this luxury rental is their pricing

reviews.text: I have moved out of Paramount for over 3 months now but never managed to get back my deposit, despite calling and emailing management and account manager multiple times. They have stopped replying to my emails in the recent weeks. Had to write this review because it ruins the whole experience.
reviews.title: Never got my deposit back.

descriptions.value: Located in the Trendy East Cut Neighborhood Steps From the Transbay Center, 500 Folsom Has Two Low Rise Buildings Bracketing a High Rise Tower With 545 Residential Units.​ Approximately 6,000 Sf of Premium Designed, Ground Floor Retail Space Offers Incredible Opportunity for Today’s Best Retailers.​

Soaring 42 stories into the air from the heart of San Franciscos vibrant East Cut neighborhood, 500 Folsom's brand new apartments offer luxury high-rise living amid a host of shopping, dining, employment, and public transportation options. Just two blocks to the Transbay Transit Center and with a 96 Walk Score, here you will find the best of the city is always within easy reach. At 500 Folsom, it's easy to see that vision lives here.Our residential tower is comprised ofnbspbrand newnbspstudio, 1-, and 2-bedroom apartment homes, including premium penthouses and townhome-style layouts. Each thoughtfully designed residence is finished in upscale style with quartz countertops, stainless steel appliances, and hardwood-style floors. Select homes boast a private balcony and stunning Bay or city views.Around our new community, take advantage of a variety of vibrant social spaces and amenities including two amazing view decksBay Terrace North and Bay Terrace Eastas well as our spa, community gardens, state-of-the-art fitness center, and yoga and spin rooms. Underground parking, neighborhood-servicing retail, and a public paseo connecting Clementina and Folsom streets add to the ease of your East Cut lifestyle, and all of this is complemented by our helpful, concierge-style staff dedicated to ensuring that all your expectations are met.Just outside our building, walk or bike to your choice of nearby restaurants, cafs, and art galleries, or head to work at neighborhood tech giants Google, Salesforce, or Slack. When your plans call for travel beyond our neighborhood, easily access BART, Caltrain, or interstates 80 or 280 to reach the rest of the Bay Area.

Located in the trendy East Cut neighborhood steps from the Transbay Center, 500 Folsom has two low rise buildings bracketing a high rise tower with 545 residential units. Approximately 6,000 SF of premium designed, ground floor retail space offers incredible opportunity for today’s best retailers.Located in the trendy East Cut neighborhood steps from the Transbay Center, 500 Folsom has two low rise buildings bracketing a high rise tower with 545 residential units. We offer Self-Guided Tours by Appointment Only. Soaring 42 stories into the air from the heart of San Francisco's vibrant East Cut neighborhood, 500 Folsom combines the best of cosmopolitan living with all the comforts of home. The ever-ascending residential tower designed by world-renowned architectural firm Skidmore, Owings & Merrill (SOM) is comprised of luxury penthouses, studio, one-, and two-bedroom apartment homes. Each thoughtfully-designed residence is finished in contemporary style with quartz countertops, stainless steel appliances, and hardwood-style vinyl floors. Select homes boast a private balcony and stunning Bay or city views. Comprising 500 Folsom's top four floors, The Skyline Penthouse Collection features luxurious one- and two-bedroom residences spanning up to 1,366 square feet. Featuring stunning floor-to-ceiling windows with unrivaled views of the city and Bay, each penthouse apartment includes custom-designed closets by California Closets(r) and upscale finishes including gourmet kitchens with top-of-the-line GE Appliances and Caesarstone(r) quartz countertops. 500 Folsom offers a curated collection of social and wellness-centric amenities. From the comfort of the Sunset Terrace or Bay Terrace, residents can enjoy al fresco lounges, community gardens, BBQ grills and an outdoor spa, all with Bay Bridge views as the stunning backdrop. The fully appointed fitness center includes state-of-the-art equipment, a spacious yoga studio, and a HIIT Zone featuring Peloton(r) bikes and TRX(r) Training rack system. The pet-friendly community also includes an indoor Paw Spa. Centered at the heart of the up-and-coming East Cut neighborhood, 500 Folsom is located in San Francisco's new urban heartbeat. Well-maintained public spaces, renowned restaurants, an enriched arts landscape, and globally-celebrated employers infuse the neighborhood with an enlivened and magnetic energy, inviting San Franciscans to live, work, and play.

reviews.title: Management doesn’t live up to their word

reviews.text: On apartments.com, it said that the company is offering 2 months free. Then during the tour, the agent said that I will get an opportunity to get 6 weeks off if application is made within 24 hours. And then past business hours on the same day, I get a text to make a decision before midnight. If this is how management makes decisions, I don't know if I feel safe with other decisions that the management makes. I will not recommend 500 Folsom to any of my friends because the management will not uphold to their words and can change on me anytime

descriptions.value: Office building located in Downtwon San Francisco, CA.

The East Cut has forged a new identity in recent years and is San Francisco’s fastest-growing and most exciting new neighborhood.​ The East Cut, which covers about seven square blocks is San Francisco’s first high-rise, dense, walkable neighborhood.​ It includes several of San Francisco’s most luxurious glass condominium towers, and home to large offices for companies such as Facebook, LinkedIn and Salesforce.​ The centerpiece of the neighborhood is the 5.4-acre Salesforce Park, an elevated green space built atop a bus terminal and reachable by elevator or gondola from below.​ The park is a quiet reprieve from the high-rises that surround it, with grassy lawns and curving paths.​ There’s plenty of programming as well, from yoga classes to toddler play groups.​  With newly designed pedestrian plazas and streetscapes, and the East Cut’s central location — adjacent to SOMA and the financial district, it is easily the neighborhood people are flocking to.​

reviews.text: Be careful renting in this building. The lofts are extremely hot. I can't get my bedroom below 72 degrees even though I have a 14000 BTU AC unit in place. It took management 12 months to approve the portable AC unit and now they are refusing to pay for it. It is usually much warmer. It can be as much as 20 degrees hotter than the outside temperature. It took 6 months for management to address a non-functional stove. They finally replaced it when I informed them that I would do it myself and deduct the cost of the new stove top from my rent. I have requested a rent decrease based on the loft bedroom being so hot that it is unusable and market conditions, which have driven rents down. It is usually much warmer. It can be as much as 20 degrees hotter than the outside temperature. Their response was to invite me to vacate because I complained too much. This was communicated in writing by the owner with no regard of how expensive moving is. I asked if my unit was hot before I leased it. I was told NO.

descriptions.value: Traditional tenant mix

Colliers International as Exclusive Advisors to the Seller, are pleased to present the opportunity to acquire 153 Kearny Street / 217 Sutter Street, commonly referred to as 153 Kearny Street (“the Property”).​ This is an excellent opportunity for an investor to own a leased asset located at the intersection of Union Square and the Financial District, two highly desirable San Francisco commercial districts with incredibly high barriers to entry.​ The Property is a retail commercial condominium, approximately 26,324 square feet, comprised of ±11,050 square feet at the ground level, ±10,696 square feet in a lower level, and ±4,578 square feet on a mezzanine.​ There is potential to increase the current square footage on the Mezzanine level by an additional ±3,291, providing future ownership the ability to capture additional income.​ The building in which the Property is located was originally constructed in 1909, totaling approximately 85,000 square feet, and was “condominiumized” in 1996.​ There are currently two (2) tenants under lease, Walgreens and 7-Eleven.​ Both tenants have closed the stores, but remain subject to rent.​ Walgreens’ lease expires July 31, 2031 and 7-Eleven’s lease expires March 31, 2024.​ The leases are net, both tenants are responsible for taxes and insurance.​ The tenants occupy the entire ground level, the mezzanine and a portion of the basement, the remaining portion of the basement (± 7,146sf) is currently unoccupied.​ The Property benefits from tremendous exposure in a high-traffic location with excellent street frontage on two major thoroughfares.​ It is surrounded by high-end retailers, restaurants, office towers, and other amenities.​ The Property is located within two (2) blocks of major public transit, including BART & Muni.​ Neighboring areas include Union Square, South of Market (SOMA), Jackson Square, and the Financial District.​

For registration requirements and regulations, please review here or contact Alexsis Aguirre | 949-799-4658 | aaguirre@crexi.​com.​ Cushman & Wakefield Retail Investment Advisors is excited to offer 153 Kearny Street, a unique value-add retail auction/investment opportunity located at the high-traffic corner of Kearny and Sutter Streets in San Francisco, CA.​ The Property is 17,620 SF, plus there is 1,444 SF of additional mezzanine and 6,800 SF of additional basement.​ TOUR DATES: Property tours are available on November 14th, 15th, and 21st by appointment only.​ Please contact the listing broker to schedule a tour.​ AUCTION TIMELINE/PROCESS: The Property is offered unpriced and offers will be received & evaluated via a live online Auction.​ The auction, conducted by Crexi.​com, will take place from 11/27/23 until 11/29/23.​ Due diligence materials are available now on-line following a prospective purchaser’s execution of a Confidentiality Agreement.​ All offers must be made on a non-contingent basis with a nonrefundable deposit and proof of funds necessary to complete the transaction.​ The closing will take place on 12/28/23.​ INVESTMENT SUMMARY: The offering provides investors, developers, or users the opportunity to reimagine and reposition this iconic retail location while receiving more than seven years of in-place, credit-quality income (or possibly strategically negotiating an early lease buyout with Walgreen’s).​ The Property is L-shaped with street-front frontage on two highly trafficked and retail-tenanted streets in downtown San Francisco.​ The Property is a highly visible retail condominium interest occupying the ground floor, mezzanine, and basement of a successfully leased boutique office building.​ In addition, near-term increases in NOI can be realized upon the releasing of the 2,265 SF suite at 217 Sutter Street, which was formerly occupied by 7-Eleven and has rent due until March 2024.​ ​ Non-Contingent ​ Earnest Money Deposit: Greater of $20,000 or 10% of the Purchase Price ​ Marketing Fee: 3% of the Winning Bid Amount, $20,000 minimum ​ $10,000 Participation Deposit Required  153 Kearny St and 217 Sutter St, San Francisco, CA 94108

descriptions.value: Marcus & Millichap is pleased to communicate a $1,500,000 pricing correction to the marketplace. 2001 Van Ness Avenue is a value-add four-story office building well-located on San Francisco’s Van Ness Avenue. Built in 1920, the 27,281 SF mixed-use property occupied by a mix of retail, full floor, and private office suites of varied sizes. There is significant opportunity to increase rents and decrease expenses through an aggressive, hands-on management strategy. Improvements to suite interiors and possible suite aggregation at lease expiration paired with a competitive leasing program will afford the eventual purchaser significant growth in rental income. Both listing agents are available to answer questions and set tour times. Please reach out to discuss in detail. 2001 Van Ness’s four stories are comprised of two floors of office over the garage level, all resting atop ground floor retail. The ground floor consists of three retail suites and an elevator lobby which serves the three above-grade floors, garage included. The second-floor garage level is comprised of 22 unobstructed, striped, spaces. To maximize parking, an additional 4 cars can be parked in tandem while still maintaining convenient ingress and egress for all other vehicles. The current ownership employs a garage management company who in turn employs one full-time attendant at the subject property during business hours. Although this allows the garage to hold more cars (±20 visitor vehicles throughout each business day) it does not cover the cost of employing the parking management service and the expense should be removed. Our underwriting omits this expense as well as the associated visitor parking income. More detail on the second-floor parking level is available on pages 18-19. Additional clarity can be provided by the listing agents. The subject property features reinforced masonry construction as well as a reinforced concrete foundation. The property’s roof is flat with a built-up top surface and has an HVAC system with roof-mounted condensers paired with 20-ton air handlers to service split units. The current ownership has completed significant property improvements totaling over $400,000 in the last 24 calendar months. Improvements include but are not limited to exterior painting, coating, sealant, rehabilitation, new roof and substantial roof upgrades, air conditioner replacement and upgrade, elevator hydraulic system repair and upgrade, elevator car repair and upgrade plus cosmetic upgrades, lobby door security upgrades & security camera upgrades, garage door repairs, and other assorted improvements and repairs. In addition, the property will benefit directly from the in-progress Van Ness Improvement Project. This substantial civic improvement will deliver San Francisco its first Bus Rapid Transit system, a globally proven solution to improve transit service on bustling urban arterials. To maximize the community benefit, the project includes extensive utility maintenance, safety enhancements, and other civic improvements along the corridor such as wider, better lit pedestrian walkways that should help revitalize the historic corridor and encourage additional foot traffic. This investment opportunity offers a sophisticated investor the chance to increase income and decrease expenses through an aggressive, hands-on management strategy. Improvements to suite interiors and possible suite aggregation at lease expiration, paired with an aggressive leasing program, should afford the eventual purchaser significant growth in rental income, bringing the average property rents in line with achieved rents in similar quality properties along the Van Ness corridor.

Our Pacific Heights location is a neighborhood coworking space for professionals who want to work near home. We are located on the west side of Van Ness, where Pacific Heights, Nob Hill and Polk Gulch intersect. We offer safe & private furnished offices to accommodate single users, but also teams of up to 20 people. Full-time offices come fully-furnished and start at $799/month and provide a productive and secure work environment designed to help you focus and create.

The location is close to many restaurants, shops, and public transportation – all in the core of the Van Ness beautification project. Supportive landlord willing to offer a new long term lease to the right operator. Marcus & Millichap is proud to present to the marketplace the opportunity to purchase the fee simple interest in 2001 Van Ness, a four-story office building well-located on San Francisco’s Van Ness Avenue. Built in 1920, the 27,281 SF mixed-use property is virtually 100% occupied by a mix of retail, full floor, and private office suites of varied sizes. The only suite to be delivered vacant is a ±500 SF office suite occupied by the current ownership. 2001 Van Ness’s four stories are comprised of two floors of office over the garage level, all resting atop ground floor retail. The ground floor consists of three retail suites and an elevator lobby which serves the three above-grade floors, garage included. The second-floor garage level is comprised of 22 unobstructed, striped, spaces. To maximize parking, an additional 4 cars can be parked in tandem while still maintaining convenient ingress and egress for all other vehicles. The current ownership employs a garage management company who in turn employs one full-time attendant at the subject property during business hours. Although this allows the garage to hold more cars (±20 visitor vehicles throughout each business day) it does not cover the cost of employing the parking management service and the expense should be removed. Our underwriting omits this expense as well as the associated visitor parking income. More detail on the second-floor parking level is available on pages 18-19. Additional clarity can be provided by the listing agents. The subject property features reinforced masonry construction as well as a reinforced concrete foundation. The property’s roof is flat with a built-up top surface and has an HVAC system with roof-mounted condensers paired with 20-ton air handlers to service split units. The current ownership has completed significant property improvements totaling over $400,000 in the last 24 calendar months. Improvements include but are not limited to exterior painting, coating, sealant, rehabilitation, new roof and substantial roof upgrades, air conditioner replacement and upgrade, elevator hydraulic system repair and upgrade, elevator car repair and upgrade plus cosmetic upgrades, lobby door security upgrades & security camera upgrades, garage door repairs, and other assorted improvements and repairs. In addition, the property will benefit directly from the in-progress Van Ness Improvement Project. This substantial civic improvement will deliver San Francisco its first Bus Rapid Transit system, a globally proven solution to improve transit service on bustling urban arterials. To maximize the community benefit, the project includes extensive utility maintenance, safety enhancements, and other civic improvements along the corridor such as wider, better lit pedestrian walkways that should help revitalize the historic corridor and encourage additional foot traffic. The exterior of this retail building has stunning Corinthian columns and vintage glass windows. 1350 Van Ness has a dedicated loading ramp with a new steel garage door on Bush Street. The Van Ness Improvement Project concluded in 2021, and the Bus Rapid Transit system is slated to begin running in April of 2022. Village at Sandhill Phase I is an open-air lifestyle center constructed in 2005 on 28-acres and includes 288,021 square feet anchored by JCPenney & Books-A-Million, and including national brands Victoria’s Secret, Ann Taylor Loft, Jos.​ A Banks, Lane Bryant, New York & Co.​, Bath & Body Works, Sunglass Hut and others, along with an all-star lineup of successful restaurants: Panera Bread, Blaze Pizza, Five Guys, Moe’s Southwest, Wild Wing Café, Blue Fin and Marble Slab, plus a host of other seasoned tenants.​ With below-market rents and current occupancy at just 84%, Village at Sandhill Town Center I offers investors tremendous upside at below replacement cost pricing for a high quality, high curb appeal regional retail destination in an affluent, rapidly-growing submarket in the heart of the Sunbelt.​ The subject property is the primary component of Village at Sandhill, a 300-acre mixed-use project located in Columbia’s affluent northeast suburbs at the strategic intersection of Clemson & Two Notch Roads.​ Village at Sandhill offers a true live, work, play environment in suburban Columbia with an expansive, growing trade area and easy access to the Columbia MSA via I-20 and US 1.​ Located in Columbia’s fast-growing Northeast submarket, the project provides multi-family residential, open-air retail, dining, entertainment and employment opportunities in a contemporary open air configuration.​

value: ​VILLAGE AT SANDHILL – Northeast Columbia’s hub for live, work and play. The 1.3 million square foot property includes - Home Depot, TJ Maxx, Old Navy, Shoe Carnival, Home Goods, Belk, JCPenney, Academy Sports, ULTA, MUV Fitness, Value City Furniture, Regal Cinema’s, Plex Hiwire indoor sports, Starbucks, AT&T and many more. New additions to the Village at Sandhill include Nexus Luxury Apartments with 240 units and Nexus Senior Living (under construction) with 200 units. Employers include Richland School District 2 Headquarters and Magnet School plus the new Richland County Library branch.

​DESIRABLE DEMOGRAPHICS – Located in the fastest growing residential area in Columbia MSA. Northeast Columbia population increased 130% from 53,000 to 124,000 between 2000-2017 with high average household income of $89,648 within a 3-mile radius. Median Age: 35 years.

​MEANINGFUL UPSIDE –The Subject Property is a legitimate Value-add opportunity with scale, discount-to-replacement-cost pricing and future upside. This submarket continues to show recovery & improvement driven by population growth and consumption patterns favoring this location.

​DYNAMIC RETAIL CORRIDOR – The intersection of Two Notch Rd (U.S. HWY 1) and Fashion Drive in Northeast Columbia has experienced some of the strongest retail growth in the Columbia MSA, recently adding retailers including Hobby Lobby, Fresh Market, Sam’s Club, Orange Theory Fitness, PetSupermarket, Sleep Number Beds, McAlister’s Deli, Aspen Dental, Smashburger and Zoe’s Kitchen. Retail square footage in this node is now over 2 million square feet.

​COLUMBIA, SC – The capitol city of South Carolina, home to all HQ of state government (38,000 employees), The University of South Carolina (enrollment: 34,000), U.S. Army Fort Jackson (15,000 enlisted and civilian population with $700+ million economic impact). Submarket employers include Blue Cross Blue Shield (6,800); Verizon (1,500); South Carolina Departments of Public Safety of Motor Vehicles (1,650); Trane (450).

descriptions.value: Long established as one of the most vibrant cultural destinations in San Francisco' s history, the Castro is the perfect setting for a variety of retail shops and restaurants with its ample public transportation and growing community nearby. 2390 Market Street is located at the intersection of Market and Castro; the epicenter for the city' s LGBT community. Many historical and significant landmarks still exist today, such as the Castro Theater and the LGBT History Museum, and serve as attractions for the effervescent and colorful district. As such, the Castro is considered to be one of San Francisco' s most successful tourist attractions and a boon for the local economy.

2390 Market is a multi-family home in San Francisco, CA 94114. Nearby schools include Marin Preparatory School, Spanish Infusión School and Sanchez Elementary School. The closest grocery stores are Seventeenth & Noe Groceteria, Mollie Stone's and Eureka Market. Nearby coffee shops include Hearth Coffee Roasters, Castro Coffee Company and Espressamente Illy. Nearby restaurants include Pica Pica Maize Kitchen, Orphan Andy's and SUBWAY. 2390 Market is near Jane Warner Plaza, Harvey Milk Plaza and Pink Triangle Park. This address can also be written as 2390 Market Street, San Francisco, California 94114.

The Lease has an original 15 year lease with 10+ years left on primary term and Tenant’s right to extend with 5 five-year options with 10% rent increases on each option.This extremely rare asset is situated in one of San Francisco’s hottest real estate market known as the Sunset / Parkside District. The property is located on 19th Avenue (Highway 1) which is the main highway along California’s coastline that stretches through Golden Gate Park and over the Golden Gate Bridge or to downtown San Francisco. In addition the immediate surrounding of the Sunset District area has a high average house hold income, even higher than the average income of Santa Clara County / Silicon Valley ( The wealthiest county in the United States). The property has rooftop parking (32 spaces) as well as additional parking directly across the street. Strong barriers to entry by city and surrounding area promotes beneficial supply/demand curve in favor of retail owners. By limiting overall development, existing retail benefits from high occupancy levels and higher rental rates.

descriptions.value: Sacramento Street is a street located in the Presidio Heights neighborhood of San Francisco, California.​ It is known for its Victorian and Edwardian architecture, as well as its high-end shops, restaurants, and cafes.​ The street is also home to a number of embassies and consulates, making it a hub of international activity.​ Sacramento Street is considered one of the most prestigious and upscale addresses in San Francisco and is one of the city’s most sought-after neighborhoods.​ It is known for its tree-lined streets, picturesque homes, and stunning views of the Golden Gate Bridge and San Francisco Bay.​ Many of the homes on the street have been preserved and restored, adding to its historical charm.​ In addition to its residential and diplomatic buildings, Sacramento Street also has a number of luxury shopping and dining options, including gourmet grocery stores, retail boutiques, and upscale restaurants.​ The street is also home to a number of parks and open spaces, including the Presidio, which offers hiking and biking trails, picnic areas, and panoramic views of the city.​ Overall, Sacramento Street is a vibrant and charming neighborhood that is popular among both residents and visitors alike.​

descriptions.value: 19 Joost Ave is a multi-family home in San Francisco, CA 94131. This 2,148 square foot multi-family home sits on a 1,589 square foot lot and features 3 bathrooms. This property was built in 1900. Nearby schools include Glen Park Elementary School, St John S Elementary School and St. John the Evangelist School. The closest grocery stores are Canyon Market, Buddie's Super Market and Cheese Boutique. Nearby coffee shops include Cup Cafe, Bello Coffee & Tea and Cuppa. Nearby restaurants include Viking’s Giant Submarines, Pebbles Cafe and Gialina. 19 Joost Ave is near Dorothy W. Erskine Park, Cayuga & Lamartine mini park and Sunnyside Conservatory. This address can also be written as 19 Joost Avenue, San Francisco, California 94131.

This wonderful 3 story mixed use building is located in the heart of the highly desirable Glen Park neighborhood.​ The building is comprised of 2 residential flats on Joost Street, the ground story flat is a 1 bedroom / 2 bath and the upper flat has 2 bedroom / 1 bath.​ The spacious commercial unit has a dedicated entrance on Monterey Boulevard.​ Both residential flats have tall ceilings, bright light, large decks and sweeping southerly views.​ This mixed use building is just steps to the Glen Park BART station and shopping in the village.​ It is conveniently located within the Glen Park neighborhood commercial transit district, where commercial uses are encouraged at the ground story level.​

This ground story flat is a 1 bedroom / 2 bath boasting a large deck and main living area with tall ceilings, plentiful storage and a multi-level floor plan. Just steps to the Glen Park BART station and shopping in the village. It is conveniently located within the Glen Park neighborhood commercial transit district.

Horvath & Tremblay is pleased to present the exclusive opportunity to purchase the four-family investment property located at 2320 W Armitage Avenue in the Bucktown neighborhood of Chicago, Illinois (the “Property”). The Property contains four, fully occupied, condo-quality units containing 11 bedrooms and 5 bathrooms in 5,000 square feet of building area on a 0.07-acre parcel with off-street parking. The Property is located in Bucktown, a high-density, inner-urban core neighborhood on the north side of Chicago, directly north of Wicker Park and northwest of the Loop. The transit-oriented neighborhood is readily accessible via the Blue Line and has multiple access points to the elevated Bloomingdale Trail, also known as the 606.

​LOCATION: The high-density neighborhood of Bucktown is one of Chicago's most sought-after and attractive residential neighborhoods. Bucktown is located east of Logan Square, directly north of Wicker Park and northwest of the Loop. The affluent neighborhood offers an appealing blend of tree-lined residential streets, active retail districts, neighborhood parks, and convenient public transportation. As a result of these amenities, Bucktown has become a popular cost-alternative to the nearby, and more expensive, Lincoln Park neighborhood.
​Separately Metered Electric: Each unit is separately metered for electricity, which the tenants pay directly.

​THE ASSET: 2320 W. Armitage Avenue is located in the Bucktown neighborhood of Chicago, IL. The Property contains four, fully occupied, condo-quality units containing 11 bedrooms and 5 bathrooms in 5,000 square feet of building area on a 0.07-acre parcel with off-street parking.
​New Parking Pad: A new parking pad was constructed in 2018 at the rear of the Property that offers tandem parking for 6 vehicles.
​Attractive, Low-Maintenance Brick Building: The building features a classic brick and brownstone façade with a small front yard and parlor-level entrance.
​Upgraded Units: Upgrades and highlights include stainless-steel appliances, granite countertops, original wood moldings, and vintage built-in storage.
​Large Floorplans: The spacious floorplans average over 1,250 square feet and include a separate dining room area.

​PROPERTY UPGRADES: The 3.5-story brick building has undergone extensive updating over the last 10 years. The large, full-floor, units are made up of two, 3-Bedroom/1-Bathroom Units on the 2nd and 3rd floors, a 2-Bedroom/2-Bathroom Unit on the parlor level, and a non conforming 3-Bedroom/1-Bathroom Unit on the garden level. descriptions.value: The 4,000 SF ground floor restaurant at 111 Mason is a showstopper.​ Located on the ground floor of the recently upgrade Bijou Hotel, the restaurant was renovated in 2018 and offers the unique opportunity to tap into the hotel’s clientele and attract new customers.​ This expansive space includes an additional 1200 square foot prep space on the lower level, providing ample space, and will be delivered in a fully-fixtured and clean condition.​ The wood-fired oven and Type I hood allow for a variety of concepts and the private dining space provides an intimate atmosphere for special events or VIP guests.​ The Type 47 License is available for tenant use at no cost, providing an added bonus for those looking to implement a sophisticated cocktail menu.​ 111 Mason Street is located at the entrance to Union Square and across from San Francisco’s best new restaurant of 2022.​ It enjoys good foot traffic, but also finds itself situated near public transportation and several parking garages.​ Neighbors include prominent restaurants like Kin Khao (Michelin rated) and Bodega (winner of San Francisco’s best new restaurant in 2022 by Eater SF)
Office zoned land in Walker, MI.​ This site has prominent frontage, a peaceful setting, and is only 1.2 miles from I-196 and 28th St.​ Ideal setting for a corporate headquarters.​

descriptions.value: AVAILABLE FOR IMMEDIATE OCCUPANCY EXCEPTIONAL LOCATION within The Portola District’s main shopping corridor—San Bruno Avenue. This spacious property is situated in San Francisco’s sunny southeastern neighborhood surrounded by a diversely popular array of cafés, diners, bakeries, delicatessens and markets. PROPERTY HIGHLIGHTS Great corner location on vibrant San Bruno Avenue suitable for retail or restaurant Great Exposure for Building and Signage Opportunity Excellent Window Lining Offers Plenty of Natural Lighting Primarily Open Floor Plan with High Ceiling 2 Double-Door Entries 2 Updated Restrooms 1 Block from Public Parking Lot Former SF Public Library Nearby neighbors include Bank of America, Walgreens, O'Reilly Auto Parts, Sterling Bank, Bank of the West, Subway, Round Table Pizza, Four Barrell Coffee and many other restaurants and business services. View by appointment only.

Marcus & Millichap is pleased to bring to market 2450 San Bruno Avenue in San Francisco, California. This offering presents a rare opportunity for investors and owner-users to acquire a pride of ownership asset in a highly sought after location. The Subject Property is located on the busy signalized intersection of San Bruno Ave and Sillman Street in the vibrant Portola District of San Francisco. Property enjoys great exposure and visibility with an immediate access to and from Highway 101. 2450 San Bruno Avenue is a three story multi-tenant building zoned NC2- Neigborhood Commercial. First floor of the property is an excellent retail space with a large showroom and high ceilings (used to be SF Library) enjoying San Bruno Avenue's busy foot traffic. Second and third floors are offices of professional services providers with great scenic views and natural lighting. Property has an elevator as well as +/- 1,000 SF of Developable Office Spaces on the third floor, which adds to the overall upside of the investment. City of San Francisco remains to be one of the highly sought-after investment destinations in the world. With one of the lowest office vacancy in the Nation and high barriers of entry, this market continues to be a highly favorable destination location among investors, developers, and owner-users. DISCLAIMER: The information contained herein has been obtained from sources we believe to be reliable; however Marcus & Millichap has not verified, and will not verify, any of the information contained herein, nor has Marcus & Millichap conducted any investigation regarding these matters and makes no warranty or representation whatsoever regarding the accuracy or completeness of the information provided. All potential buyers must take appropriate measures to verify all of the information set forth herein. AERIAL VIDEO: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XOgvvDceBdw&feature=youtu.be
